{
  "doc_id": "50057",
  "text": "Andrographis paniculata, commonly known as green chiretta or, in Indonesian, as sambiloto, is a medicinal plant often used in Indonesia for treating diabetes. The plant tastes very bitter so is known as 'king of bitters' . Its major biological activity is antidiabetic [CITATION_1] but it has also been reported to have anti-angiogenetic [CITATION_2] , antibacterial [CITATION_3] , anti-cancer [CITATION_4] , anti-inflammatory [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] , antimalarial [CITATION_7] , antioxidant [CITATION_8] , and hepatoprotective activities [CITATION_9] .",
